description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for Band 5 Staff Nurses who have an interest in Health Visiting to work with the Health Visiting Teams across North Ceredigion . Full time preferred but part time hours will be considered. The posts will be fixed term for 2 years. The post holder will need to be committed to developing a high degree of standards of care and actively seek and promote professional working relationships with other statutory and voluntary practitioners. The post holder will be responsible for the assessment of health needs and the development, implementation and evaluation of programmes of care to meet the needs of the child and their family.&lt;br /&gt;In order to apply you will need to possess a Registered Children Nurse Qualification or an Adult Registered Nurse Qualification. The prior would be preferable and be registered in the appropriate part of the NMC.&lt;br /&gt;The successful candidate will be expected to work towards the competencies required to apply for the Health Visiting SCPHN course within two years of being in post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to travel between sites in a timely manner is essential and you will need to travel out of Aberystwyth for your initial training and induction. Please demonstrate your ability to fulfil this criteria in your application.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hywel Dda delivers on the criteria set by the Welsh Government Healthy Child Programme and the Baby Friendly Initiative.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; English and/or Welsh speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews will be held on 23/11/2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameSian JonesJob titleHealth Visitor Team LeaderEmail addresssian.jones9@wales.nhs.ukTelephone number07980 278826&lt;/p&gt;
